Diagnosis.
Carapace relatively broad (
Fig. 60
). Pseudorostral spines long, diverging (
Fig. 60
). Median row with 2 median gastric spines; 2 cardiac spines; 2 intestinal spines (
Fig. 60
). Basal antennal article with 2 relatively long distal spines, strongly diverging (
Fig. 61G
). Ischium of third maxilliped long (
Fig. 63E–H
). Ambulatory legs (notably merus and propodus) relatively long (
Figs. 60
, 
65I–K
). Male telson appears semicircular (
Fig. 64E
). G1 very long, strongly curved, slender, tip bent inwards (
Fig. 67A–D
).
